10.1 Why Type Hints Matter
Type hints make Python code more readable, maintainable, and help catch errors before runtime. They‚Äôre especially valuable in larger codebases and team environments.
# Without type hints - unclear what types are expected
def calculate_discount(price, discount_rate, is_member):
    if is_member:
        discount_rate += 0.05
    return price * (1 - discount_rate)

# With type hints - crystal clear
def calculate_discount_typed(price: float, discount_rate: float, is_member: bool) -&gt; float:
    """Calculate discounted price with member bonus."""
    if is_member:
        discount_rate += 0.05
    return price * (1 - discount_rate)

